Berau, Indomobil Sukses, Jasa Marga: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-03-09T02:04:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/berau-indomobil-sukses-jasa-marga-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 0.5 percent to 3,580.31.  Coal producers: Indonesia cut the reference price for coal
sales in March by 3.6 percent from a month earlier to $122.43 a
metric ton, the Energy and Mineral Resources Ministry said in a
statement on its website today.  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ),  Asia ’s largest exporter of
power-station coal, gained 2.5 percent to 3,050 rupiah. PT Adaro
Energy (ADRO IJ), Indonesia’s second-largest coal producer, rose
1.1 percent to 2,400 rupiah.  State companies: Indonesia may allow state-owned companies
to pay lower dividends to the government starting from this year
to help boost expansion, Investor Daily Indonesia reported,
citing State Enterprises Minister Mustafa Abubakar.  PT Telekomunikasi  Indonesia  (TLKM IJ), Indonesia’s largest
telephone company, fell 0.7 percent to 7,300 rupiah and PT Bank
Mandiri (BMRI IJ), the nation’s biggest bank by assets, rose 0.8
percent to 6,400 rupiah.  PT Berau Coal Energy (BRAU IJ): The company’s unit, Berau
Capital Resources Ltd., has offered to buy back guaranteed
senior notes it sold in July 2010, Berau said in a statement to
exchange. Berau sold $350 million of five-year dollar-
denominated notes in July 2010, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg News. Berau, an Indonesian coal producer, was
unchanged at 530 rupiah.  PT Indomobil Sukses Internasional (IMAS IJ): The company’s
unit, PT Indomobil Finance Indonesia, plans to sell 500 billion
rupiah ($56.8 million) of bonds in the second quarter this year
to fund lending, Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing
Gunawan, a director at the company. Indomobil Sukses, an
automotive retailer, declined 0.7 percent to 7,050 rupiah.  PT Jasa Marga (JSMR IJ): The government is planning to
increase tariffs at several toll roads in September to help
attract investors, Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing
Public Works Minister Djoko Kirmanto. Jasa Marga, the nation’s
biggest toll-road operator, was unchanged at 3,275 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
